Nessun host noto da address-object" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FFE0B2;strokeColor=#E65100;align=center;fontSize=10;verticalAlign=top;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="1060" y="530" width="250" height="80" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="cdmz" value="" style="endArrow=none;html=1;strokeColor=#333333;strokeWidth=2;" edge="1" parent="1" source="po7" target="dmzL2"><mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="gstL2" value="&lt;b&gt;OPT/Guest — segmento P8&lt;/b&gt;
Dominio di broadcast separato
DNS pubblici 8.8.8.8 / 8.8.4.4

Probabile AP guest (no traffico inter-zona)
Applicabile &lt;b&gt;guest_ppp&lt;/b&gt; PPPoE con account
OPT_PPPoE_ACCOUNT" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FFF59D;strokeColor=#F57F17;align=left;fontSize=10;spacingLeft=8;verticalAlign=top;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="1060" y="660" width="250" height="240" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="cgst" value="" style="endArrow=none;html=1;strokeColor=#333333;strokeWidth=2;" edge="1" parent="1" source="po8" target="gstL2"><mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="leg" value="&lt;b&gt;Protocolli e parametri Layer 2 in uso&lt;/b&gt;
• Ethernet IEEE 802.3 — full-duplex 1 Gbit/s su tutte le RJ45  • MTU 1500 ovunque  • Hardware-watchdog attivo  • Software-watchdog 60 s
• Nessun VLAN tagging configurato sul firewall (no interfacce vlanX); eventuali VLAN sono mantenute sullo switch a valle
• CAPWAP per gestione AP  • PPPoE disponibile su wan1/wan2 (shutdown) e attivo come opzione su guest_ppp  • LLDP / PoE: lato switch" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#E8EAF6;strokeColor=#3F51B5;align=left;fontSize=10;spacingLeft=10;verticalAlign=top;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="30" y="940" width="1290" height="60" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="exp" value="&lt;b&gt;Nota importante sul mapping ge ↔ porta fisica ↔ port-group&lt;/b&gt;
• &lt;b&gt;interface-name&lt;/b&gt; assegna solo un &lt;i&gt;label&lt;/i&gt; alla porta logica (es. ge5 = “lan2”).
• &lt;b&gt;port-grouping&lt;/b&gt; stabilisce quale interfaccia logica controlla ciascuna porta fisica e raggruppa più porte in un bridge.
• Effetto: P4, P5 e P6 — pur essendo etichettate ge4/ge5/ge6 come lan1/lan2/dmz — sono tutte bridged nell'interfaccia &lt;b&gt;lan1&lt;/b&gt; (10.61.10.1/19).
• Le interfacce lan2 (10.61.200.0/24) e l'iface “reserved” non hanno porte fisiche → sono interfacce &lt;b&gt;routed-only&lt;/b&gt; raggiunte via L3." style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FFEBEE;strokeColor=#C62828;strokeWidth=2;align=left;fontSize=10;spacingLeft=10;verticalAlign=top;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="30" y="1020" width="1290" height="80" as="geometry"/></mxCell></root></mxGraphModel></diagram><diagram id="p3" name="3. Layer 3 (OSI)"><mxGraphModel dx="2200" dy="1500" grid="1" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="1500" pageHeight="1170" math="0" shadow="0"><root><mxCell id="0"/><mxCell id="1" parent="0"/><mxCell id="t" value="Vista Layer 3 (OSI) — IP, subnet, routing, NAT, VPN logica" style="text;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=18;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#1F2937;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="200" y="10" width="1300" height="30" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="s" value="Topologia IP così come il firewall la conosce: subnet locali, route statiche, NAT, tunnel come path logici" style="text;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=12;fontStyle=2;fontColor=#475569;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="200" y="42" width="1300" height="20" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="int" value="INTERNET
